{"id":"d=origam-topic-4082//p=af0338716ae14dc0a36a065ce8395748","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-4082"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["17f8a84ed89a4f9cac5f9e08d501907b"],"__file_part":["6b64dd0bf3b146cf96c4806e7b2b33f8"],"__part_n":["0"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"topicId":["4082"],"categoryId":["61"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-work-with-application-documentation/4082"],"title":["How to work with application documentation"],"imagesFound":["6"],"imagesDescribed":["6"],"imageUrl":["https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/3/3c4f984fc8522d125ea587c30e014fc5fe85af93.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/7/79812c234fa6f5fd4e6859a0fd53281d38911914.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/0/0be9f20717611d3576dea323568b1c8c861bfdf4.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/2/2f2d7d082a31e5c89bcfaeefe3e2688c52561264.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/f/f859c1a1b10e9d89d398d2a45f9a50b330b64b3c.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/d/d8362a9c524cdd914038c8ad2df00ade43a3cdc0.png"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":"# How to work with application documentation\n\nURL: https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-work-with-application-documentation/4082\n\n@vikter (2025-05-13 11:33:42Z):\n   \n This tutorial shows how to work with the user documentation that is part of the client application. \n   Documentation elements \n You can use the following documentation elements: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/3/3c4f984fc8522d125ea587c30e014fc5fe85af93.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface for a documentation management tool, featuring a dropdown menu labeled \u0022Category\u0022 with various selectable options. The visible options include: USER_SHORT_HELP, USER_LONG_HELP, USER_WFSTEP_DESCRIPTION, DEV_INTERNAL, RULE_EXCEPTION_MESSAGE, EXAMPLE, EXAMPLE_JSON, and EXAMPLE_XML. There\u0027s also a text field adjacent to the dropdown that shows a default value of \u0022(null)\u0022. The overall purpose of this interface appears to be for categorizing and documenting information within a software application.\n\n\n  \n \n USER_LONG_HELP: Field tooltip \n USER_WFSTEP_DESCRIPTION: Workflow step title for UI steps (visible to users) \n DEV_INTERNAL: Internal note for modeler/developer \n RULE_EXCEPTION_MESSAGE: Additional exception message for rules \n EXAMPLE: General example of use \n EXAMPLE_JSON: Example of JSON input or output used in APIs \n EXAMPLE_XML: Example of XML used in transformations or workflows \n \n   Documentation Modification \n If you want to create documentation for a specific object, you must first select it in the Model Browser. \nRemember: documentation elements are linked to the object selected in the  Model Browser , not in the  Property editor . \n Once you\u2019ve selected the object, all available documentation elements appear in the right panel under the  Documentation  tab. If the panel is not visible, you can activate it in the main menu under  View  /  Documentation . \n You can now fill in all the desired elements, placing each one on a separate line: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/7/79812c234fa6f5fd4e6859a0fd53281d38911914.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface (UI) window titled \u0022Documentation.\u0022 This window contains a table with two columns: \u0022Category\u0022 and \u0022Text.\u0022 In the table, one entry is listed under the \u0022Category\u0022 as \u0022USER_SHORT_HELP\u0022 and its corresponding \u0022Text\u0022 reads \u0022Person or Company name.\u0022 The UI features several tabs or buttons at the bottom, specifically including \u0022Packages,\u0022 \u0022Model Browser,\u0022 \u0022Properties,\u0022 \u0022Output,\u0022 \u0022Find Results,\u0022 and highlighted in red is the \u0022Documentation\u0022 tab. The purpose of this interface appears to be for managing or referencing documentation related to user help or information in a software application.\n\n\n  \n To delete an element, select and remove the entire line. \n When you\u2019re finished, don\u2019t forget to save your changes. \nThe documentation editor has its own save button that must be used: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/0/0be9f20717611d3576dea323568b1c8c861bfdf4.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface section labeled \u0022Documentation.\u0022 In this section, there is a table with two columns: \u0022Category\u0022 and \u0022Text.\u0022 The row contains the entry \u0022USER_SHORT_HELP\u0022 under the Category column and \u0022Person or Company name\u0022 under the Text column. Additionally, there is an icon represented by a disk save symbol highlighted in red to the left of the row. The purpose of this interface appears to be for managing documentation entries related to user help or information about individuals or organizations.\n\n\n  \n   Client Application \n Here are some examples showing how documentation elements appear in the client application. \n Tooltip: \n  \n Workflow step: \n \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/2/2f2d7d082a31e5c89bcfaeefe3e2688c52561264.png]\nDescription: The image appears to be a user interface for creating periodic invoices. At the top, there is a section labeled \u0022Create Periodic Invoices.\u0022 The central focus is the header \u0022Select dates and locations,\u0022 highlighted in red. Below, there are labeled fields for the invoice period, including \u0022From\u0022 and \u0022To,\u0022 with a specified date of \u002230.04.2025.\u0022 There is also a field labeled \u0022Invoicing Party\u0022 that likely allows selection from a dropdown. Visible buttons include \u0022Cancel\u0022 and \u0022Next,\u0022 indicating progression in the invoicing process. The purpose of this interface is to enable users to set the timeframe and details for invoicing in a systematic manner.\n\n\n  \n \n\n","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:56:23"},"vector":[-0.031856332,-0.021590792,-0.06129235,0.017908392,-0.00063260086,-0.046152055,0.006706694,-0.002269125,0.006387815,-0.003257367,0.01544122,-0.0037561636,0.025534805,-0.013441547,-0.024391387,-0.008045222,-0.0042599924,0.0028731783,0.034153458,-0.00080174266,0.027624808,-0.0044484115,0.03653926,0.017646633,0.014387362,0.01676093,-0.016770648,-0.015347074,0.031247104,-0.007154835,-0.0019191215,-0.020745827,-0.019116791,-0.0022367479,-0.031096648,0.025072992,0.003102218,0.01790162,-0.04030328,0.032141842,0.009790961,-0.015529386,-0.01679445,-0.0065749483,0.03174388,-0.031875245,-0.018213786,0.006403367,0.012051766,-0.026260497,-0.045396432,-0.012429757,0.03664836,-0.06457288,0.041864134,0.017047364,-0.046601422,-0.03855197,-0.07043424,0.049939074,0.008540072,-0.004089597,0.015301901,-0.056702595,-0.00093236536,0.03853388,-0.0034530796,0.0004384316,-0.02535178,-0.026004879,0.011320638,0.03464975,-0.04635763,-0.0053317407,-0.07101745,-0.004205703,-0.00019282244,0.013634915,-0.037937228,0.019541876,-0.03127044,0.00782772,0.00011917054,-0.009253867,-0.011865699,-0.0031698497,-0.004218595,0.06624945,0.017753078,0.056582887,-0.026784293,-0.013373093,0.082990006,-0.00015263996,-0.0256697,-0.006062586,-0.021436697,0.0022313136,0.003990157,0.014807772,-0.022216193,-0.025409399,0.02028687,0.014818459,-0.030813057,-0.019474627,0.033143044,0.0008211406,0.011120656,-0.040270716,-0.006640444,0.001112152,0.023976358,-0.002371482,0.024953911,0.012947882,0.00820628,-0.012398327,0.020291744,0.01318252,0.00039651728,0.014547871,0.017438618,-0.011358554,-0.0008793649,0.014467944,0.020835355,0.06515119,0.012043923,0.0009207041,0.025684433,-0.012645758,-0.013318361,0.013671648,-0.03224061,-0.014420257,0.05801057,0